<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head><%- include('partials/head') %></head>
<body>

<%- include('partials/nav') %>

<section class="page-hero page-hero-sm">
  <div class="section-inner text-center">
    <div class="section-label">Legal</div>
    <h1 class="page-hero-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="page-hero-sub">Last updated: January 2025</p>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="legal-body">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="legal-content">

      <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
      <p>KeyDog provides cloud-hosted key and access credential management software ("the Service"). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect information when you use the Service or visit our website at keydog.io.</p>

      <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
      <p><strong>Account information:</strong> Name, email address, institution name, and role — collected when you contact us or when your account is created.</p>
      <p><strong>Usage data:</strong> Log data including IP addresses, browser type, pages visited, and actions taken within the Service. This is used solely for security, diagnostics, and service improvement.</p>
      <p><strong>Data you enter:</strong> Key records, staff records, door records, audit entries, and any other data you create within the Service. This data belongs to you.</p>

      <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To provision and operate your account</li>
        <li>To respond to support and sales inquiries</li>
        <li>To send transactional emails (login details, alerts, reports you configure)</li>
        <li>To diagnose errors and improve the Service</li>
        <li>To comply with legal obligations</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do not sell your data to third parties. We do not use your data for advertising.</p>

      <h2>4. Data Storage and Security</h2>
      <p>Your data is stored on managed cloud infrastructure with encryption at rest and in transit. Each customer's data is stored in an isolated database. We apply access controls, regular backups, and security monitoring. No system is perfectly secure; we will notify you promptly in the event of a breach affecting your data.</p>

      <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>We retain your data for as long as your account is active and for 30 days after termination to allow data export. Audit log retention within the Service depends on your plan (30 days to 5 years). You may request deletion at any time by contacting us.</p>

      <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, export, or delete personal data we hold about you. To exercise any of these rights, email us at <a href="mailto:privacy@keydog.app">privacy@keydog.app</a>.</p>

      <h2>7. Cookies</h2>
      <p>Our marketing website uses no third-party tracking cookies. The Service application uses a session cookie strictly necessary for authentication. We do not use advertising or analytics cookies.</p>

      <h2>8. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>We use a small number of sub-processors to deliver the Service, including cloud hosting and transactional email. Each is bound by data processing agreements consistent with applicable privacy law. We do not share your data beyond what is necessary to operate the Service.</p>

      <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify account holders of material changes by email. Continued use of the Service constitutes acceptance.</p>

      <h2>10. Contact</h2>
      <p>Privacy questions? Email <a href="mailto:privacy@keydog.app">privacy@keydog.app</a> or write to us via our <a href="/contact">contact form</a>.</p>

    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>

</body>
</html>
